    "Firstly, it directly impacts the accuracy and reliability of the model's output, which in turn affects user trust-particularly critical in applications involving sensitive or impactful information dissemination [6]- [9].",
    "Secondly, in non-English LLMs such as Kimi, linguistic nuances and cultural context play a significant role in the model's performance and its error profile [10], [11].",
    "Effective error correction mechanisms can mitigate risks associated with misinterpretations or inappropriate responses, which are more pronounced in models dealing with less-represented languages.",
    "C. Aims and ScopeThe objective of this article is to explore the implementation of automated error correction and feedback loops within Kimi to enhance its accuracy and reliability.",
    "This research aims to fill a gap in current LLM error management strategies by proposing a system that not only detects errors post hoc but also corrects them in real time, without the need for frequent retraining."
